The paper deals with distributed block source coding theory, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the characterization of a sum-rate-distortion function, which is a topic in data compression and signal processing (cs.DS). The paper also discusses convex-geometric properties, which are relevant to optimization and geometry (cs.SI). The amplewise Boolean AND function is used as an example, which is a topic in multimedia and image processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement of the one-message Wyner-Ziv rate-distortion function, which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
